Many are the headings in the classified section of that first directory which seems odd to us today.
                    Here are a few noticed: Axes; Balances; Bar and Rod Iron; Basket Stores; Bathing Rooms; Bellows;
                    Blacksmith Shops; Brittania-ware; Buckskin Goods; Buffalo Robes; Carriages and Wagons; Cooper Shops;
                    Glove makers; Gunsmiths; Hubs and Spokes; Japanned-ware; Lamps and Oil; Livery, Sale and Boarding
                    Stables; and Paper Collars.

